data.enText: to officially tell sb that you are leaving your job, an organization, etc.

data.chText: 八年后，他辞去了经理的职务。
data.enText: He resigned as manager after eight years.

data.chText: 董事会的两名成员辞职以示抗议。
data.enText: Two members resigned from the board in protest.

data.chText: 我父亲去年辞去了董事的职务。
data.enText: My father resigned his directorship last year.
to accept sth unpleasant that cannot be changed or avoided
She resigned herself to her fate.

data.chText: 我们只好接受销售造成的亏损。
data.enText: We had to resign ourselves to making a loss on the sale.

data.enText: We had to resign ourselves to making a loss on the sale.

example: He resigned himself to his fate

tr: part with a possession or right
example: I am relinquishing my bedroom to the long-term house guest
resign a claim to the throne

tr: leave (a job, post, or position) voluntarily
example: She vacated the position when she got pregnant
The chairman resigned when he was found to have misappropriated funds

tr: give up or retire from a position
example: The Secretary of the Navy will leave office next month
The chairman resigned over the financial scandal

value.def: If you resign from a job or position, you formally announce that you are leaving it.

example.ex: A hospital administrator has resigned over claims he lied to get the job...
example.tran: 一位医院的管理人员辞职了，因为有人指责他为了得到这份工作而撒了谎。

example.ex: Mr Robb resigned his position last month.
example.tran: 罗布先生上个月辞职了。

value.def: If you resign yourself to an unpleasant situation or fact, you accept it because you realize that you cannot change it.

example.ex: Pat and I resigned ourselves to yet another summer without a boat...
example.tran: 我和帕特在没有船的情况下勉强又凑合了一个夏天。

example.ex: He had resigned himself to watching the European Championships on television.
example.tran: 他只好将就着在电视上看欧洲锦标赛。

value.tran: 屈从;顺从;安于;勉强接受

value.boxu_tran: 不要混淆resign和retire。resign指辞职，可以发生在任何年龄，也可能很快就开始从事另一个工作。但retire表示退休，是指到了一定的年龄可以领取养老金而停止工作。职业运动员退役，即使年龄还很小，也可以使用retire。
value.boxu_usage: Do not confuse resign and retire. If someone resigns from their job, they leave it after saying that they do not want to do it any more. You can resign from your job at any age, and perhaps start another job soon afterwards. When someone retires, they leave their job and stop working, often because they have reached the age when they can get a pension. When professional sportsmen and women stop playing sport as their job, you can also say that they retire, even if they are fairly young.
